description: From Latin biennium, from biennis (“2-year”) + -ium (“forming abstract nouns”), from bi- (“two”) + annus (“year”), q.v.

entries.meaning: A period of two years, particularly for purposes involving intercalation or fiscal calculations.
examples: Coordinate terms: annum, triennium, quadrennium, quinquennium, sexennium, septennium, octennium, novennium, decennium, centennium, quincentennium, millennium, decamillennium, centimillennium, millionennium
